  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>Administrator Audit Logs provide comprehensive monitoring and tracking of all system activities. This includes user actions, administrative changes, security events, and system operations. Audit logs are essential for security monitoring, compliance reporting, troubleshooting issues, and maintaining accountability across the platform.</p>

  <h3>Access Requirements</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Administrator Role</strong> — Must be logged in with admin privileges</li>
    <li><strong>Audit Data Access</strong> — Full access to all audit log entries and filtering</li>
    <li><strong>Security Monitoring</strong> — Authority to monitor system security events</li>
    <li><strong>Compliance Reporting</strong> — Ability to generate audit reports for compliance</li>
    <li><strong>Direct Access</strong> — Available via `/admin/audit-logs`</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Audit Log Capabilities</h3>

  <h4>Activity Monitoring</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Real-time Tracking</strong> — Monitor system activities as they occur</li>
    <li><strong>Historical Analysis</strong> — Review past activities and changes</li>
    <li><strong>User Activity</strong> — Track all user login, logout, and account activities</li>
    <li><strong>Administrative Actions</strong> — Monitor all administrator operations and changes</li>
    <li><strong>Security Events</strong> — Track security-related incidents and responses</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Compliance & Reporting</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Audit Trails</strong> — Complete audit trails for regulatory compliance</li>
    <li><strong>Report Generation</strong> — Generate detailed audit reports</li>
    <li><strong>Data Export</strong> — Export audit data for external analysis</li>
    <li><strong>Retention Management</strong> — Manage audit log retention periods</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Accessing Audit Logs</h3>

  <h4>From Admin Dashboard</h4>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Open Admin Dashboard</strong> — Navigate to `/admin/dashboard`</li>
    <li><strong>Click Audit Logs Card</strong> — Click on the "Recent Activity" or audit-related statistics card</li>
    <li><strong>Access Audit Logs</strong> — Click "View Audit Logs" link in the card footer</li>
    <li><strong>View Activity Stream</strong> — See recent system activities and events</li>
  </ol>

  <h4>Direct Navigation</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Direct URL</strong> — Go directly to `/admin/audit-logs`</li>
    <li><strong>Admin Menu</strong> — Access through administrator navigation menu</li>
    <li><strong>Quick Actions</strong> — Shortcuts from security alerts or system notifications</li>
    <li><strong>Search Results</strong> — Access from audit log search and filter results</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Viewing Audit Log Entries</h3>

  <h4>Audit Log Interface</h4>

  <h5>Audit Log Columns</h5>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Timestamp</strong> — Date and time when the activity occurred</li>
    <li><strong>User</strong> — User who performed the action (if applicable)</li>
    <li><strong>Action</strong> — Type of action performed (create, update, delete, login, etc.)</li>
    <li><strong>Resource</strong> — System resource affected (user, club, carnival, etc.)</li>
    <li><strong>Resource ID</strong> — Specific identifier of the affected resource</li>
    <li><strong>Details</strong> — Additional information about the activity</li>
    <li><strong>IP Address</strong> — IP address from which the action was performed</li>
    <li><strong>User Agent</strong> — Browser/client information</li>
  </ul>

  <h5>Log Display Features</h5>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Chronological Order</strong> — Entries displayed with most recent first</li>
    <li><strong>Pagination</strong> — Navigate through large volumes of audit entries</li>
    <li><strong>Page Size Control</strong> — Adjust number of entries displayed per page</li>
    <li><strong>Auto-refresh</strong> — Option to automatically refresh log display</li>
    <li><strong>Export Options</strong> — Export filtered results for external analysis</li>
  </ul>

